parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Dim Headlights due to Reflector Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dim headlights can cause accidents or injuries due to reduced visibility, especially at night or in low-light conditions, posing a significant safety risk to the driver, passengers, and other road users.
symptoms: making it difficult or impossible to see the road ahead
especially at night or in low-light conditions; the headlights do not illuminate the roadway; the low beam reflector is foggy or oxidized
reducing light output; the headlights are barely visible
